---
Mafdet's interest in the Oath-Crossing is maritime-legal: it established that cities can create shared jurisdiction over contested territory through documented oath rather than conquest or institutional succession.
The Shrine of the First Claw considers the Oath-Crossing an exemplary oath form: witnessed, documented, with specific obligations and a designated arbitration mechanism.
An oath's value is not measured by the frequency of its enforcement but by whether it changed the parties' behavior. The Oath-Crossing demonstrably ended active territorial competition between Midgaard and Kowloon. By Shrine standards, it is working.
Mafdet's Claw Mark Registry notates Great Northern Forest-origin cargo as verified under Oath-Crossing joint jurisdiction: joint certification means two attestation systems apply, producing higher commercial trust than either alone.

